{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880699261,"sessionID":"ses_28543363cffehqsG3wvgFfF9nN","part":{"id":"prt_d7abcf882001dNZt6KkFstYrwW","messageID":"msg_d7abceaf0001g5VgfAv06QMV7g","sessionID":"ses_28543363cffehqsG3wvgFfF9nN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_f603527f801949e68ed7479b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PCAP analyzer example application in the AgentCube `example` module.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-037\n10: - **Module**: `example`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Files to Add\n18: \n19: | Path | Description | Type |\n20: |------|-------------|------|\n21: | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application with SandboxRunner, ReActAgent, Planner, and Reporter | New |\n22: | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Dependencies: fastapi, uvicorn, langchain-openai, scapy | New |\n23: | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition | New |\n24: | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest | New |\n25: | `example/pcap-analyzer/README.md` | Usage documentation | New |\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Files to Modify\n30: \n31: | Path | Description | Change Type |\n32: |------|-------------|-------------|\n33: | | | |\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## Files to Delete\n38: \n39: | Path | Description |\n40: |------|-------------|\n41: | | |\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## Requirements\n46: \n47: ### AR-037-001: PCAP Analyzer Module Structure\n48: \n49: The system SHALL provide a complete `example/pcap-analyzer/` module demonstrating AgentCube SDK usage.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: AR-037-001-A — Module directory exists\n52: \n53: - **GIVEN** the workspace root at `example/`\n54: - **WHEN** the directory is inspected\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap-analyzer/` subdirectory with all required files\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: AR-037-001-B — Required files present\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory\n60: - **WHEN** files are listed\n61: - **THEN** it SHALL contain `pcap_analyzer.py`, `requirements.txt`, `Dockerfile`, `deployment.yaml`, and `README.md`\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ### AR-037-002: PCAP Analyzer FastAPI Application\n66: \n67: The system SHALL provide a FastAPI application that orchestrates PCAP analysis.\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-A — Application startup with API key\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY` environment variable\n72: - **WHEN** the application completes startup hooks\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL initialize LLM client, PLANNER agent, and REPORTER agent\n74: - **AND** bind to `0.0.0.0:8000`\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-B — Application startup without API key\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` is started without a valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n79: - **WHEN** the application attempts startup\n80: - **THEN** startup SHALL fail with an error rather than serve requests\n81: \n82: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-C — Analyze endpoint accepts file upload\n83: \n84: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n85: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with a PCAP file upload (`pcap_file` as `UploadFile`)\n86: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: AR-037-002-D — Analyze endpoint accepts path parameter\n89: \n90: - **GIVEN** a running service with valid LLM configuration\n91: - **WHEN** a client calls `POST /analyze` with `pcap_path` form field (alternative to file upload)\n92: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return `AnalyzeResponse` with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ### AR-037-003: SandboxRunner Integration\n97: \n98: The system SHALL provide a `SandboxRunner` class that encapsulates AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient.\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-A — SandboxRunner initialization\n101: \n102: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is constructed with name, namespace, router_url, workload_manager_url, and warmup_sec\n103: - **WHEN** initialization completes\n104: - **THEN** it SHALL create a `CodeInterpreterClient` instance\n105: - **AND** be ready to execute commands via `run()`, upload files via `upload_file()`, and can be stopped via `stop()`\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-B — Context manager support\n108: \n109: - **GIVEN** `SandboxRunner` is used as a context manager\n110: - **WHEN** the block exits (with or without exception)\n111: - **THEN** the underlying CodeInterpreterClient SHALL be properly stopped\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-C — File upload to sandbox\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** a local PCAP path to analyze\n116: - **WHEN** `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` is called\n117: - **THEN** the file SHALL be uploaded to the remote sandbox\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: AR-037-003-D — Command execution in sandbox\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxRunner` with an active session\n122: - **WHEN** `run(command)` is invoked\n123: - **THEN** the runner SHALL execute the command in the remote sandbox context and return execution result\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ### AR-037-004: LLM Orchestration (Planner + Reporter)\n128: \n129: The system SHALL implement LLM-based orchestration for PCAP analysis.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: AR-037-004-A — Planner agent generates analysis script\n132: \n133: - **GIVEN** a PCAP file is available in the sandbox\n134: - **WHEN** the PLANNER agent receives analysis request with context about the file\n135: - **THEN** it SHALL generate a Python script using scapy to analyze the PCAP\n136: - **AND** return the script as a string\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: AR-037-004-B — Reporter agent generates human-readable report\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** analysis results from sandbox execution\n141: - **WHEN** the REPORTER agent receives the raw results\n142: - **THEN** it SHALL generate a human-readable analysis report\n143: - **AND** return the report as a string\n144: \n145: #### Scenario: AR-037-004-C — ReAct agent coordinates flow\n146: \n147: - **GIVEN** a running PCAP analyzer service\n148: - **WHEN** a client submits a PCAP for analysis\n149: - **THEN** the ReAct agent SHALL orchestrate: upload file → generate script → execute → generate report\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### AR-037-005: PCAP Analyzer Configuration\n154: \n155: The system SHALL read configuration from environment variables with appropriate defaults.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: AR-037-005-A — Default configuration values\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** the service starts with only `OPENAI_API_KEY` set\n160: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL use:\n162:   - `OPENAI_API_BASE`: default `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1`\n163:   - `OPENAI_MODEL`: default `Qwen/QwQ-32B`\n164:   - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`: default `my-interpreter`\n165:   - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`: default `default`\n166:   - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`: default `5`\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: AR-037-005-B — Environment variable overrides\n169: \n170: - **GIVEN** environment variables `OPENAI_API_BASE`, `OPENAI_MODEL`, `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`, `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`, `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` are set\n171: - **WHEN** the service starts\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL use the provided values instead of defaults\n173: \n174: #### Scenario: AR-037-005-C — Required environment variables\n175: \n176: - **GIVEN** the service starts without `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ROUTER_URL`, or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n177: - **WHEN** the application attempts to start\n178: - **THEN** it SHALL raise a configuration error indicating the missing required variables\n179: \n180: ---\n181: \n182: ### AR-037-006: PCAP Analyzer Dependencies\n183: \n184: The system SHALL provide a `requirements.txt` with pinned dependency versions.\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: AR-037-006-A — Dependency file content\n187: \n188: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt`\n189: - **WHEN** dependencies are inspected\n190: - **THEN** it SHALL include at minimum: `fastapi>=0.120.0`, `uvicorn`, `langchain-openai`, `scapy`, `agentcube-sdk`\n191: - **AND** all versions SHALL be pinned or have compatible version specifiers\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ### AR-037-007: PCAP Analyzer Container Image\n196: \n197: The system SHALL provide a Dockerfile for building the analyzer container.\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: AR-037-007-A — Dockerfile base and entrypoint\n200: \n201: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` is built\n202: - **WHEN** the container runs without overriding the command\n203: - **THEN** it SHALL use a Python base image, set appropriate `PYTHONPATH`, expose port `8000`, and run the FastAPI application\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: AR-037-007-B — SDK vendoring\n206: \n207: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile build context includes the agentcube SDK\n208: - **WHEN** the image is built\n209: - **THEN** it SHALL include the SDK in the image for the application to import\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### AR-037-008: PCAP Analyzer Kubernetes Deployment\n214: \n215: The system SHALL provide a Kubernetes deployment manifest.\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: AR-037-008-A — Deployment manifest structure\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml`\n220: - **WHEN** applied to a cluster\n221: - **THEN** it SHALL create a Deployment with appropriate container image, port, and resource configuration\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: AR-037-008-B — Environment variable wiring\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** the deployment is applied\n226: - **WHEN** the pod starts\n227: - **THEN** it SHALL have required environment variables configured:\n228:   - `OPENAI_API_KEY` (from secret)\n229:   - `OPENAI_API_BASE`\n230:   - `OPENAI_MODEL`\n231:   - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`\n232:   - `ROUTER_URL`\n233:   - `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME`\n234:   - `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE`\n235:   - `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC`\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ### AR-037-009: SDK Integration\n240: \n241: The system SHALL use the AgentCube Python SDK for code interpreter operations.\n242: \n243: #### Scenario: AR-037-009-A — SDK import\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** `pcap_analyzer.py` runs analysis\n246: - **WHEN** it needs to execute code in a sandbox\n247: - **THEN** it SHALL import `CodeInterpreterClient` from `agentcube.code_interpreter`\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: AR-037-009-B — Context manager usage\n250: \n251: - **GIVEN** `CodeInterpreterClient` is used in `SandboxRunner`\n252: - **WHEN** the runner enters context manager\n253: - **THEN** it SHALL create a session via ControlPlaneClient and initialize data plane\n254: - **AND** when exiting context, it SHALL properly stop and delete the session\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: AR-037-009-C — SDK exception handling\n257: \n258: - **GIVEN** remote command returns non-zero exit code in JSON\n259: - **WHEN** `execute_command` processes the response\n260: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `CommandExecutionError` (from `agentcube.exceptions`) with `exit_code`, `stderr`, and `command` attributes\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ### AR-037-010: PCAP Analysis Workflow\n265: \n266: The system SHALL execute a complete PCAP analysis workflow.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: AR-037-010-A — Complete analysis flow\n269: \n270: - **GIVEN** a running PCAP analyzer service with all required configuration\n271: - **WHEN** a client uploads a valid PCAP file to `/analyze`\n272: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n273:   1. Upload the PCAP file to the sandbox\n274:   2. Generate analysis Python script via PLANNER\n275:   3. Execute the script in the sandbox\n276:   4. Collect execution results\n277:   5. Generate human-readable report via REPORTER\n278:   6. Return response with `script`, `results`, and `report` fields\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: AR-037-010-B — Invalid PCAP file handling\n281: \n282: - **GIVEN** a client uploads a file that is not a valid PCAP\n283: - **WHEN** the analysis is attempted\n284: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating the file is not a valid PCAP\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: AR-037-010-C — Large file handling\n287: \n288: - **GIVEN** a client uploads a PCAP file exceeding reasonable size limits\n289: - **WHEN** the upload is attempted\n290: - **THEN** the system SHALL return an error indicating file size limit exceeded\n291: \n292: ---\n293: \n294: ## Acceptance Criteria\n295: \n296: - [ ] AC001: `example/pcap-analyzer/` directory contains all required files\n297: - [ ] AC002: FastAPI application starts successfully with valid `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n298: - [ ] AC003: FastAPI application fails to start without `OPENAI_API_KEY`\n299: - [ ] AC004: `/analyze` endpoint accepts file upload and returns AnalyzeResponse\n300: - [ ] AC005: `/analyze` endpoint accepts path parameter as alternative\n301: - [ ] AC006: SandboxRunner provides upload_file, run, and stop methods\n302: - [ ] AC007: SandboxRunner supports context manager protocol\n303: - [ ] AC008: PLANNER agent generates Python script using scapy\n304: - [ ] AC009: REPORTER agent generates human-readable report\n305: - [ ] AC010: ReAct agent orchestrates the complete analysis flow\n306: - [ ] AC011: Configuration uses defaults when env vars are not set\n307: - [ ] AC012: Required environment variables are validated at startup\n308: - [ ] AC013: requirements.txt contains all required dependencies\n309: - [ ] AC014: Dockerfile builds successfully and runs the application\n310: - [ ] AC015: Kubernetes deployment manifest is valid and deployable\n311: - [ ] AC016: SDK exceptions are properly handled\n312: - [ ] AC017: Invalid PCAP file returns appropriate error\n313: - [ ] AC018: README.md contains usage instructions\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## Configuration Changes\n318: \n319: | Key | Old Value | New Value | Description |\n320: |-----|-----------|-----------|-------------|\n321: | | | | |\n322: \n323: ---\n324: \n325: ## Database Schema Changes\n326: \n327: | Table | Change | SQL |\n328: |-------|--------|-----|\n329: | | | |\n330: \n331: ---\n332: \n333: ## API Changes\n334: \n335: ### New APIs\n336: \n337: | Method | Path | Description |\n338: |--------|------|-------------|\n339: | POST | `/analyze` | Analyze PCAP file with LLM orchestration |\n340: \n341: ### Modified APIs\n342: \n343: | Method | Path | Description |\n344: |--------|------|-------------|\n345: | | | |\n346: \n347: ### Deprecated APIs\n348: \n349: | Method | Path | Description |\n350: |--------|------|-------------|\n351: | | | |\n352: \n353: ---\n354: \n355: ## Architecture Notes\n356: \n357: ### Key Components\n358: \n359: | Component | Path | Description |\n360: |------|------|-------------|\n361: | Main Application | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | FastAPI application entry point |\n362: | SandboxRunner | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | AgentCube CodeInterpreterClient wrapper |\n363: | Planner Agent | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | LLM agent for generating analysis scripts |\n364: | Reporter Agent | `example/pcap-analyzer/pcap_analyzer.py` | LLM agent for generating reports |\n365: | Dependencies | `example/pcap-analyzer/requirements.txt` | Python package dependencies |\n366: | Container | `example/pcap-analyzer/Dockerfile` | Container image definition |\n367: | Deployment | `example/pcap-analyzer/deployment.yaml` | Kubernetes deployment manifest |\n368: \n369: ### Environment Variables\n370: \n371: | Variable | Default | Required | Description |\n372: |----------|---------|----------|-------------|\n373: | `OPENAI_API_KEY` | - | Yes | OpenAI-compatible API key |\n374: | `OPENAI_API_BASE` | `https://api.siliconflow.cn/v1` | No | API endpoint |\n375: | `OPENAI_MODEL` | `Qwen/QwQ-32B` | No | Model name |\n376: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | - | Yes | AgentCube Workload Manager URL |\n377: | `ROUTER_URL` | - | Yes | AgentCube Router URL |\n378: | `CODEINTERPRETER_NAME` | `my-interpreter` | No | Code interpreter name |\n379: | `SANDBOX_NAMESPACE` | `default` | No | Kubernetes namespace |\n380: | `SANDBOX_WARMUP_SEC` | `5` | No | Sandbox warmup duration |\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## References\n385: \n386: - Proposal: `changes/AR-037/proposal.md`\n387: - SDK design: `python-sdk/design.md`\n388: - SDK spec: `python-sdk/spec.md`\n389: - Reference source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`\n\n(End of file - total 389 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-037: PCAP 分析器示例应用 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the PCAP analyzer example application in the AgentCube `example` module.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-037\n- **Module**: `example`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n- **Reference Sources**: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/example/pcap-analyzer/`, `python-sdk/design.md`, `python-sdk/spec.md`\n\n---\n\n## Files to Add\n\n| Path | Description | Type |\n|------|-------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-037/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775880699240,"end":1775880699258}}}}
